    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Coinlike objects made of wood, originally produced as emergency money then only for commemorative, souvenir, or advertising purposes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000012271/Doty, Macmillan Encyclopedic Dictionary of Numismatics (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Objetos con forma de monedas hechas de madera, originalmente producidas como dinero de emergencia y luego sólo con propósitos conmemorativos, publicitarios o como recuerdos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
